records.nl_statement: Show that the collection $\{(a,b) \mid a < b, a \text{ and } b \text{ rational}\}$ is a basis that generates a topology different from the lower limit topology on $\mathbb{R}$.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Filter Set TopologicalSpace
open scoped Topology
records.ground_truth:
def lower_limit_topology (X : Type) [Preorder X] :=
  generateFrom {S : Set X | ∃ a b, a < b ∧ S = Ico a b}

theorem exercise_13_8b (T : Set (Set ℝ))
  (hT : T = {S : Set ℝ | ∃ a b : ℚ, a < b ∧ S = Ioo ↑a ↑b}) :
  IsTopologicalBasis T ∧
  generateFrom T ≠
  lower_limit_topology ℝ :=
